Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.86,0:00:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the museum you'll see dazzling examples of birds and reptiles
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.68,0:00:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that occur in almost every environment on planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.96,0:00:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They're at home on land, in the sea, even in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.56,0:00:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they've adapted over hundreds of millions of years to be at home in that environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.32,0:00:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Sensing Evolution trail you'll see how small variations from one generation to the next
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.04,0:00:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,can add up to very big changes over long periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.84,0:00:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Animal life first emerged in the oceans hundreds of millions of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.02,0:00:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually some animals were able to live on land
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.04,0:00:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because they evolved hard, scaly skins which didn't dry out so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.60,0:00:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They also got the ability to lay eggs on the ground with hard, protective shells.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.72,0:00:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,These were the reptiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.06,0:00:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's birds and reptiles evolved from an ancient lizard-like creature
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.76,0:00:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which looked something like the common lizard you can see in the centre of the Sensing Evolution table.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.00,0:00:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This process began around 320 million years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.48,0:01:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then they have adapted into all of the many forms you can see around the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.92,0:01:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,
